items.hint: Reference

According to GTD Reference folder is right place for topics that dont contain any actionable information Its not something that seems to have some strategic importance or urgency so we capture it and thats it However if this isnt carried out properly it can jeopardize the rest of our GTD system and therefore our personal productivity
items.title: According to GTD 'Reference' folder is right place for topics that don't contain any actionable information. Its not something that seems to have some strategic importance or urgency, so we capture it and thats it. However, if this isnt carried out properly it can jeopardize the rest of our GTD system and, therefore, our personal productivity.
